<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1964894-what-purpose-did-nirmal-s-diary-serve">What purpose did Nirmal&#39;s diary serve ?
because many things Kanai know but didn&#39;t tell anyone (exception : when he talk to Horen about Horen&#39;s last trip to Morchigipi island ).</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1964894'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F4950.The_Hungry_Tide">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1964894-what-purpose-did-nirmal-s-diary-serve">8 months ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1964894-what-purpose-did-nirmal-s-diary-serve">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/55905238-regina"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1525594915i/55905238._UX100_CR0,3,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/55905238-regina">Regina</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">According to the diary itself Nirmal intended to leave an account of the events happening in these islands, seemingly expecting that Kanai might use i<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">According to the diary itself Nirmal intended to leave an account of the events happening in these islands, seemingly expecting that Kanai might use it for some social/literary work, but I think we might also take it as a kind of defense for not being taken by Kanai – whom he appreciated - as the mentally ill man he was seen by his wife in his last days. Anyway, l would simply take it that the author needed someone to tell the whole events from a personal point of view, as they are a central point of the history of the sundarbans. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

