<span id="freeTextContainer1845860946063891496">Reading this book made me realise that I really want to see the Sundarbans some day! <br/>However, I had many issues with this book. Like pointless letters from the past and an almost sleazy male protagonist. And at one point it felt like this was going to be a love quadrangle.<br/>So yes, the setting of the book is brilliant. But I didn’t much care for the story and some of the characters. I might have liked it more if this book was only about Fokir and Piya! </span>

          </span>
        </div>


